1
00:00:05,737 --> 00:00:10,277
Nietzsche once said
facetiously,

2
00:00:10,277 --> 00:00:14,563
“If I were to believe in God,
He would have to be a good dancer!”

3
00:00:14,692 --> 00:00:17,728
[Reality is Dancing]

4
00:00:17,898 --> 00:00:22,050
I recall visiting with Śrīla Guru Mahārāj
in the afternoon one day,

5
00:00:22,050 --> 00:00:24,831
and he’s sitting in his chair, 
like that, [tapping]

6
00:00:24,831 --> 00:00:27,273
as he would do sometimes,
he’d go like this, and

7
00:00:27,273 --> 00:00:29,717
when he was very happy …

8
00:00:33,118 --> 00:00:35,159
I gave my daṇḍavats
and sat there, and he said,

9
00:00:35,173 --> 00:00:39,440
“I say, the Ultimate Reality
must be dancing.

10
00:00:39,440 --> 00:00:43,830
What do you say?”
[Laughing]

11
00:00:43,830 --> 00:00:46,859
I thought, “The Ultimate Reality 
must be dancing,

12
00:00:46,859 --> 00:00:50,589
what do I say?
[Laughing]

13
00:00:50,589 --> 00:00:53,266
He said, “I say, the Ultimate Reality
must be dancing,

14
00:00:53,266 --> 00:00:57,246
what do you say?”
[Laughing]

15
00:00:58,877 --> 00:01:02,106
Of course, 
it was a rhetorical question.

16
00:01:05,558 --> 00:01:07,554
And Guru Mahārāj explaining …

17
00:01:07,554 --> 00:01:10,637
And it’s actually on the basis
of Prema Dhāma Deva Stotram,

18
00:01:10,637 --> 00:01:12,436
but it shows us a few things.

19
00:01:12,436 --> 00:01:18,263
One is that Guru Mahārāj,
until the end of his life,

20
00:01:18,263 --> 00:01:21,968
was generating 
fresh Kṛṣṇa conscious substance.

21
00:01:22,044 --> 00:01:27,245
He wasn’t merely repeating 
what he had realised in 1941

22
00:01:29,445 --> 00:01:33,540
or 195…
Time is there irrelevant.

23
00:01:33,540 --> 00:01:37,130
He’s in a dynamic process, 
in an inner dialogue

24
00:01:37,130 --> 00:01:43,595
that was consistently, constantly,
revealing new substance.

25
00:01:46,159 --> 00:01:51,373
This is how 
Guru Mahārāj’s meditation for 50,

26
00:01:51,373 --> 00:01:57,495
70, 80, 90 years
keeps yielding nectarine substance.

27
00:01:58,476 --> 00:02:03,146
So now,
pūrṇam means ‘fulfilled’.

28
00:02:03,977 --> 00:02:10,629
Well, as he would express, 
when someone is really feeling satisfied

29
00:02:10,629 --> 00:02:15,737
or fulfilled to the nth degree—

30
00:02:15,737 --> 00:02:20,742
here, the Greek 
comes to our aid:

31
00:02:20,742 --> 00:02:26,859
ekstasis, ecstasy, means actually
‘outside of yourself’;

32
00:02:26,859 --> 00:02:30,700
you’re so happy
that you’ve become ecstatic;

33
00:02:30,700 --> 00:02:33,289
you go …
you’re outside of yourself.

34
00:02:33,289 --> 00:02:34,975
And what Guru Mahārāj
is saying here,

35
00:02:34,975 --> 00:02:39,145
“When you’re satisfied 
to the nth degree,

36
00:02:39,145 --> 00:02:43,039
and the joy cannot be contained
within yourself,

37
00:02:43,039 --> 00:02:49,579
it expresses itself 
outwards as ecstatic dance.”

38
00:02:50,615 --> 00:02:53,077
So, on the basis of this,
he’s saying,

39
00:02:53,077 --> 00:02:57,028
“The Ultimate Reality
must be dancing!”

40
00:02:59,642 --> 00:03:06,823
Reality must be dancing, 
but not in some monotonal;

41
00:03:06,823 --> 00:03:10,590
Scientific … they say, “All the atoms 
and particles are all moving,

42
00:03:10,590 --> 00:03:13,170
it’s like a dance.”

43
00:03:13,170 --> 00:03:15,151
They’re just talking 
about movement.

44
00:03:15,151 --> 00:03:17,157
But now we’re back 
to the original point.

45
00:03:17,157 --> 00:03:23,853
Guru Mahārāj would say,
“Movement enhanced with beauty is dance!”

46
00:03:23,855 --> 00:03:26,950
Just movement is not dance per se,

47
00:03:26,950 --> 00:03:30,255
but when it’s enhanced with beauty,
it’s dance.

48
00:03:30,255 --> 00:03:37,242
Speech … When the element of beauty 
is added to speech, it becomes song.

49
00:03:37,242 --> 00:03:41,063
So the better writers, 
even the better prose writers …

50
00:03:42,929 --> 00:03:45,448
Literary critics and observers,
they will say,

51
00:03:45,448 --> 00:03:49,552
“Oh, at this point in his writing, 
it approaches poetry.”

52
00:03:49,552 --> 00:03:54,062
They mean it has
a musical element to it;

53
00:03:54,062 --> 00:03:57,550
even though it’s prose, 
it’s so perfectly written,

54
00:03:57,550 --> 00:04:01,459
it’s now as if it’s being sung.

55
00:04:01,459 --> 00:04:06,413
What is the world … In that perfect world,
where we’re told,

56
00:04:06,413 --> 00:04:10,176
kathā gānaḿ nāṭyaḿ gamanam— 
[Bs: 5.56]

57
00:04:10,176 --> 00:04:15,391
“Where what they speak is like song.”
That’s what it means.

58
00:04:15,391 --> 00:04:19,265
Not that they just sing 
everything they say.

59
00:04:19,273 --> 00:04:23,167
What is being said, 
because it’s saturated

60
00:04:23,167 --> 00:04:27,927
with Reality the Beautiful—
it’s song,

61
00:04:27,967 --> 00:04:31,477
and movement is dance.

62
00:04:31,509 --> 00:04:32,270
Why?

63
00:04:32,270 --> 00:04:37,348
Because they’re under the influence 
of the Ultimate Beauty,

64
00:04:37,348 --> 00:04:39,825
Who’s also dancing.

65
00:04:39,826 --> 00:04:45,813
His ecstasy is not something
that He strives to achieve,

66
00:04:45,813 --> 00:04:49,921
like to move from the unhappy position
to a happy position—

67
00:04:49,921 --> 00:04:52,165
that’s not Kṛṣṇa!

68
00:04:52,275 --> 00:04:57,475
He’s ecstasy personified. 
He’s already ātmārāma.

69
00:04:57,475 --> 00:05:02,717
So, then the question comes up—
Viśvanāth and others deal with it—

70
00:05:02,717 --> 00:05:06,311
then why does He seem to enjoy 
His pastimes with the Vraja–gopīs?

71
00:05:06,311 --> 00:05:10,191
What is He approaching them for?
He’s already ecstasy personified.

72
00:05:10,191 --> 00:05:11,998
He’s ātmārāma.

73
00:05:11,998 --> 00:05:13,969
Various descriptions 
are given there:

74
00:05:13,969 --> 00:05:16,709
like a child playing 
with its reflection,

75
00:05:16,709 --> 00:05:19,328
one point is told, but also,

76
00:05:19,328 --> 00:05:26,562
that being ecstasy personified, 
His movements are ecstatic.

77
00:05:26,562 --> 00:05:29,706
He doesn’t move
to achieve ecstasy;

78
00:05:29,706 --> 00:05:32,216
He’s already
in an ecstatic condition,

79
00:05:32,216 --> 00:05:37,291
but He’s extending
or expanding that to others,

80
00:05:37,291 --> 00:05:45,853
particularly in Gaura-līḷā, 
Nāma-saṅkīrtan,

81
00:05:48,923 --> 00:05:51,193
and many other things.

82
00:05:51,923 --> 00:05:54,580
All of it is divine movement.

83
00:05:55,658 --> 00:06:00,539
So I thought, as Guru Mahārāj is giving 
so much sukṛti to Hegel,

84
00:06:00,539 --> 00:06:05,418
if Nietzsche met Guru Mahārāj,

85
00:06:05,418 --> 00:06:10,609
Guru Mahārāj could give him 
a concept of God that he could believe in,

86
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:14,318
that the Ultimate Reality
must be dancing.

